race.description: Retravision J P Stratton Cup Mobile Pace
race.comment: The marble has fallen best for MINSTREL NZ (2) and he is going very well having yet to miss the top-three in four starts this time in, all from wider barriers. Very brave second after working in the James Brennan Memorial last start and won two in a row here prior. Take beating from this draw. MAGNIFICENT STORM NZ (7) came from the back row when he placed in the James Brennan, just 1.2m behind Minstrel. Won three in a row here prior, one of them from this barrier. He is a danger as is MISTER SMARTEE NZ (12) who cops a second line draw this time but beat the top two picks to win the James Brennan last start, taking his record at this circuit and distance to seven from 10. PENNY BLACK NZ (1) tackles the boys but was huge without luck in the Westral Mares Classic last week. Has been in terrific form this campaign and gets the ace draw.
